5 SECTION 1.2.(b) G.S. 105-153.5A(a) reads as rewritten:
6 "(a) State Net Operating Loss. – A taxpayer's State net operating loss for a taxable year is
7 the amount by which business deductions for the year exceed gross income for the year as
8 determined under the Code adjusted as provided in G.S. 105-153.5 and G.S. 105-153.6. The
9 amount of a taxpayer's State net operating loss must also be determined in accordance with the
10 following modifications:
11 (1) No State net operating loss deduction shall be allowed.
12 (2) The amount deductible on account of losses from sales or exchanges of capital
13 assets shall not exceed the amount includable on account of gains from sales
14 or exchanges of capital assets.
15 (3) The exclusion provided by Code section 1202 shall not be allowed.
16 (4) No deduction shall be allowed under G.S. 105-153.5(a1) for the child
17 deduction.
18 (5) The deductions which are not attributable to a taxpayer's trade or business
19 shall be allowed only to the extent of the amount of the gross income not
20 derived from such trade or business.
21 (6) Any deduction under Code section 199A shall not be allowed.
22 (7) The amount of the taxpayer's excess business loss, as defined under the
23 provisions of section 461(l) of the Code, shall be fully allowed as a State net
24 operating loss."
25 SECTION 1.2.(c) Subsection (a) of this section is effective when the Part becomes
26 law and applies retroactively to taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2022. Subsection
27 (b) of this section is effective for taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2025. The
28 remainder of this section is effective when the Part becomes law.
29 SECTION 1.3.(a) G.S. 105-160.2 reads as rewritten:
30 "§ 105-160.2. Imposition of tax.
31 (a) Scope. – The tax imposed by this Part applies to the taxable income of estates and
32 trusts as determined under the provisions of the Code except as otherwise provided in this Part.
33 The taxable income of an estate or trust is the same as taxable income for such an estate or trust
34 under the provisions of the Code, adjusted as provided in G.S. 105-153.5 and G.S. 105-153.6,
35 except that the adjustments provided in G.S. 105-153.5 and G.S. 105-153.6 are apportioned
36 between the estate or trust and the beneficiaries based on the distributions made during the
37 taxable year. G.S. 105-153.6.
38 (b) Tax Base. – The tax is computed on the amount of the taxable income of the estate or
39 trust that is for the benefit of a resident of this State, or for the benefit of a nonresident to the
40 extent that the income (i) is derived from North Carolina sources and is attributable to the
41 ownership of any interest in real or tangible personal property in this State or (ii) is derived from
42 a business, trade, profession, or occupation carried on in this State. For purposes of the preceding
43 sentence, taxable income and gross income is computed subject to the adjustments provided in
44 G.S. 105-153.5 and G.S. 105-153.6. G.S. 105-153.6 and is apportioned and allocated to this State
45 under G.S. 105-130.4.
46 (c) Tax Rate. – The tax on the amount computed above is at the rate levied in
47 G.S. 105-153.7. The fiduciary responsible for administering the estate or trust shall pay the tax
48 computed under the provisions of this Part.
49 (d) Adjustments. – For the purposes of this section, the adjustments provided in
50 G.S. 105-153.5 and G.S. 105-153.6 are apportioned between the estate or trust and the
51 beneficiaries based on the distributions made during the taxable year."
