24 SECTION 1.5. G.S. 105-163.6 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 105-163.6. When employer must file returns and pay withheld taxes.
26 …
27 (c) Monthly. – An employer who withholds an average of at least two hundred fifty
28 dollars ($250.00) but less than two thousand dollars ($2,000) of State income taxes from wages
29 each month must file a return and pay the withheld taxes on a monthly basis. A return for the
30 months of January through November is due by the 15th day of the month following the end of
31 the month covered by the return. A return for the month of December is due the following January
32 31.
33 (d) Semiweekly. – An employer who withholds an average of at least two thousand
34 dollars ($2,000) of State income taxes from wages each month shall must file a return by the date
35 set under the Code for filing a return for federal employment taxes attributable to the same wages
36 and shall on a quarterly basis. A quarterly return covers a calendar quarter and is due by the last
37 day of the month following the end of the quarter. The employer also must pay the withheld State
38 income taxes by the date set under the Code for depositing or paying federal employment taxes
39 attributable to the same wages. The date set by the Code for depositing or paying federal
40 employment taxes shall be determined without regard to § 6302(g) of the Code.
41 An extension of time granted to file a return for federal employment taxes attributable to
42 wages is an automatic extension of time for filing a return for State income taxes withheld from
43 the same wages, and an extension of time granted to pay federal employment taxes attributable
44 to wages is an automatic extension of time for paying State income taxes withheld from the same
45 wages. An employer who pays withheld State income taxes under this subsection is not subject
46 to interest on or penalties for a shortfall in the amount due if the employer would not be subject
47 to a failure-to-deposit penalty had the shortfall occurred in a deposit of federal employment taxes
48 attributable to the same wages and the employer pays the shortfall by the date the employer would
49 have to deposit a shortfall in the federal employment taxes.forth below:
50 (1) If an employer's payday falls on a Wednesday, Thursday, or Friday, the
51 withheld taxes must be paid on or before the following Wednesday.
