13 PART II. CONFORM TO FEDERAL SYSTEM FOR AUDITING PARTNERSHIPS
14 SECTION 2.(a) Part 2 of Article 4 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes is amended
15 by adding a new section to read:
16 "§ 105-154.2. Federal partnership adjustments.
17 (a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this Part:
18 (1) Administrative adjustment request. – An administrative adjustment request
19 filed by a partnership under section 6227 of the Code.
20 (2) Audited partnership. – A partnership subject to a partnership level audit
21 resulting in a federal partnership adjustment.
22 (3) Corporate partner. – A partner that is subject to tax under Part 1 of this Article.
23 (4) Direct partner. – A partner that holds a direct interest in a partnership subject
24 to a federal partnership adjustment.
25 (5) Exempt partner. – A partner that is not subject to State income tax under this
26 Article that holds a direct interest in a partnership subject to a federal
27 partnership adjustment.
28 (6) Federal partnership adjustment. – A change or correction arising from a
29 partnership level audit or an administrative adjustment request that affects the
30 calculation of a taxpayer's State tax.
31 (7) Federal partnership representative. – The person the partnership designates for
32 the taxable year as the partnership's representative, or the person the Internal
33 Revenue Service has appointed to act as the federal partnership representative,
34 pursuant to section 6223(a) of the Code.
35 (8) Final federal partnership adjustment. – A federal partnership adjustment that
36 is final. A federal partnership adjustment is final when the federal partnership
37 adjustment is not subject to administrative or judicial review. If the federal
38 partnership adjustment results from filing an administrative adjustment
39 request, the federal partnership adjustment is final when the administrative
40 adjustment request is filed. Additionally, a federal partnership adjustment
41 relating to a partnership level audit is deemed final in the following
42 circumstances:
43 a. The taxpayer has received a partnership level audit from the Internal
44 Revenue Service for the tax period and the taxpayer does not timely
45 file an administrative appeal with the Internal Revenue Service.
46 b. The taxpayer consented to any of the partnership level audit findings
47 for the tax period and through a final decision or other written
48 agreement with the Internal Revenue Service all rights of appeal have
49 been waived or exhausted.
50 (9) Indirect partner. – A beneficiary of an estate or trust or an owner in a
51 partnership or pass-through entity, where the estate, partnership, pass-through
Page 4 DRH10248-SVxf-3B

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 entity, or trust holds, either itself or through another indirect partner, a direct
2 interest, in a partnership or pass-through entity subject to a final federal
3 partnership adjustment.
4 (10) Partnership level audit. – An audit of a partnership by the Internal Revenue
5 Service pursuant to Subchapter C of Title 26, Subtitle F, Chapter 63 of the
6 Code, as enacted by the Bipartisan Budget Act of 2015, Public Law 114-74,
7 which results in federal partnership adjustments.
8 (11) Reviewed year. – The taxable year of a partnership that is subject to a
9 partnership level audit from which federal partnership adjustments arise.
10 (12) State partnership representative. – The federal partnership representative
11 unless the partnership designates another person as its State partnership
12 representative. The Secretary is authorized to establish procedures for
13 designating a person, other than the federal partnership representative, to be a
14 State partnership representative.
15 (13) Tiered partner. – An estate, partnership, S Corporation, or trust that is a partner
16 in a partnership subject to a federal partnership adjustment.
17 (b) General Rule. – Except in the case of a final federal partnership adjustment that is
18 required to be reported to the Secretary using the procedures in subsection (c) of this section, a
19 partner must report and pay any State income tax due in accordance with the provisions of
20 G.S. 105-130.20 or G.S. 105-159.
21 (c) Reporting a Final Federal Partnership Adjustment. – Except for the distributive share
22 of adjustments that have been reported as required by subsection (b) of this section and an audited
23 partnership that has made a timely election under subsection (d) of this section, a partnership and
24 a partner must report a final federal partnership adjustment as follows:
25 (1) No later than 90 days after the final federal partnership adjustment, a
26 partnership doing business in this State must do both of the following:
27 a. File an income tax return reflecting the partnership's final federal
28 partnership adjustments, as modified by G.S. 105-153.5 and
29 G.S. 105-153.6, and any other information required by the Secretary,
30 and pay the additional amount due under G.S. 105-154(d) and
31 G.S. 105-154.1.
32 b. Notify each of its direct partners of the direct partner's distributive
33 share of the final federal partnership adjustments, including any
34 information necessary for the direct partner to properly file a State
35 income tax return. The information must be in the form prescribed by
36 the Secretary.
37 (2) No later than six months after the final federal partnership adjustment, each
38 direct partner subject to tax under this Article must file a State income tax
39 return reporting the direct partner's distributive share of the adjustments
40 reported to the direct partner under sub-subdivision b. of subdivision (1) of
41 this subsection, as modified by G.S. 105-153.5 and G.S. 105-153.6, and any
42 other information required by the Secretary, and pay any additional amount of
43 tax due as if the final federal partnership adjustments had been properly
44 reported.
45 (d) Election for Partnership to Pay; Exceptions. – Except as otherwise provided in
46 subdivision (2) of this subsection, an audited partnership may elect to report a final federal
47 partnership adjustment arising from a partnership level audit in the manner prescribed by the
48 Secretary. An election made under this subsection is irrevocable and cannot be made if the
49 required income tax return is not filed within the period required by this subsection. The
50 following provisions apply to an audited partnership that makes an election under this subsection:
