38 (b) Rate. – The applicable tax rates on the gross receipts from a limited possession
39 commitment are as listed in this subsection. Gross receipts does not include the amount of any
40 allowance given for a motor vehicle taken in trade as a partial payment on the limited possession
41 commitment. The maximum tax in G.S. 105-187.3(a1) on certain motor vehicles applies to a
42 continuous limited possession commitment of such a motor vehicle to the same person. The
43 applicable tax rates are as follows:
44 Type of Limited Possession Commitment Tax Rate
45 Short-term lease or rental 8%
46 Vehicle subscription 5%
47 Long-term lease or rental 3%
48 (c) Method. – A retailer who elects to pay tax on the gross receipts of the limited
49 possession commitment of a motor vehicle shall make this election when applying for a
50 certificate of title for the vehicle. To make the election, the retailer shall complete a form provided
Page 18 DRH10248-SVxf-3B

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 by the Division giving information needed to collect the alternate tax based on gross receipts.
2 Once made, an election is irrevocable.
3 (d) Administration. – The Division shall notify the Secretary of Revenue of a retailer who
4 makes the election under this section. A retailer who makes this election pays the tax under this
5 section shall report and remit to the Secretary the tax on the gross receipts of the limited
6 possession commitment of the motor vehicle. The Secretary shall administer the tax imposed by
7 this section on gross receipts in the same manner as the tax levied under G.S. 105-164.4(a)(2).
8 The administrative provisions and powers of the Secretary that apply to the tax levied under
9 G.S. 105-164.4(a)(2) apply to the tax imposed by this section. In addition, the Division may
10 request the Secretary to audit a retailer who elects to pay tax on gross receipts under this section.
11 When the Secretary conducts an audit at the request of the Division, the Division shall reimburse
12 the Secretary for the cost of the audit, as determined by the Secretary. In conducting an audit of
13 a retailer under this section, the Secretary may audit any sales of motor vehicles made by the
14 retailer."
15 SECTION 7.2.(a) G.S. 153A-156 reads as rewritten:
16 "§ 153A-156. Gross receipts tax on short-term leases or rentals.
17 (a) As a substitute for and in replacement of the ad valorem tax, which is excluded by
18 G.S. 105-275(42), a A county may levy a gross receipts tax on the gross receipts from the
19 short-term lease or rental of vehicles at retail to the general public. The tax rate shall not exceed
20 one and one-half percent (1.5%) of the gross receipts from such the short-term leases or rentals.
21 (b) If a county enacts the substitute and replacement a gross receipts tax pursuant to this
22 section, any an entity required to collect the tax shall include a provision in each retail short-term
23 lease or rental agreement noting that the percentage amount enacted by the county of the total
24 lease or rental price, excluding highway use tax, is being charged as a tax on gross receipts. For
25 purposes of this section, the transaction giving rise to the tax shall be deemed to have occurred
26 occurs at the location of the entity from which where the customer takes delivery of the vehicle.
27 The tax shall be collected at the time of lease or rental and placed in a segregated account until
28 remitted to the county.
29 …
30 (e) The following definitions in G.S. 105-187.1 apply in this section:section.
31 (1) Short-term lease or rental. – Defined in G.S. 105-187.1.
32 (2) Vehicle. – Any of the following:
33 a. A motor vehicle of the passenger type, including a passenger van,
34 minivan, or sport utility vehicle.
35 b. A motor vehicle of the cargo type, including cargo van, pickup truck,
36 or truck with a gross vehicle weight of 26,000 pounds or less used
37 predominantly in the transportation of property for other than
38 commercial freight and that does not require the operator to possess a
39 commercial drivers license.
40 c. A trailer or semitrailer with a gross vehicle weight of 6,000 pounds or
41 less.
42 …."
