20 SECTION 7.2.(c) G.S. 105-550 reads as rewritten:
21 "§ 105-550. Definitions.
22 The definitions in G.S. 105-164.3 G.S. 105-164.3, G.S. 105-187.1, and the following
23 definitions apply in this Article:
24 (1) Authority. – A regional public transportation authority or a regional
25 transportation authority created pursuant to Article 26 or Article 27 of Chapter
26 160A of the General Statutes.
27 (2) Long-term lease or rental. – Defined in G.S. 105-187.1.
28 (3) Motorcycle. – Defined in G.S. 20-4.01.
29 (4) Repealed by Session Laws 1998-98, s. 33, effective August 14, 1998.
30 (5) Public transportation system. – Any combination of real and personal property
31 established for purposes of public transportation. The systems may include
32 one or more of the following: structures, improvements, buildings, equipment,
33 vehicle parking or passenger transfer facilities, railroads and railroad
34 rights-of-way, rights-of-way, bus services, shared-ride services,
35 high-occupancy vehicle facilities, car-pool and vanpool programs, voucher
36 programs, telecommunications and information systems, integrated fare
37 systems, bus lanes, and busways. The term does not include, however, streets,
38 roads, or highways except to the extent they are dedicated to public
39 transportation vehicles or to the extent they are necessary for access to vehicle
40 parking or passenger transfer facilities.
41 (6) Short-term lease or rental. – Defined in G.S. 105-187.1.
42 (7) U-drive-it vehicle. – Defined in G.S. 20-4.01."
43 SECTION 7.2.(d) G.S. 105-551 reads as rewritten:
44 "§ 105-551. Tax on gross receipts authorized.
45 (a) Tax. – The board of trustees of an Authority may levy a privilege tax on a retailer
46 who is engaged in the business of leasing or renting U-drive-it vehicles or motorcycles described
47 in this subsection based on the gross receipts derived by the retailer from the short-term lease or
48 rental of these vehicles. The tax rate must be a percentage and may not exceed five percent (5%).
49 A tax levied under this section applies to short-term leases or rentals made by a retailer whose
50 place of business or inventory is located within the territorial jurisdiction of the Authority. This
51 tax is in addition to all other taxes. The retailers subject to this section are:
Page 20 DRH10248-SVxf-3B

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) A retailer engaged in the business of leasing or renting U-drive-it vehicles or
2 motorcycles and whose place of business or inventory is located within the
3 territorial jurisdiction of the Authority.
4 (2) A peer-to-peer vehicle sharing provider if the customer takes delivery of the
5 vehicle within the territorial jurisdiction of the Authority.
6 …."
7 SECTION 7.2.(e) G.S. 105-552 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 105-552. Collection and administration of gross receipts tax.
9 …
10 (b) Collection. – A tax levied by an Authority under this Article shall be collected by the
11 Authority but shall otherwise be administered in the same manner as the optional gross receipts
12 tax levied by under G.S. 105-187.5. Like the optional gross receipts tax, a tax levied under this
13 Article is to be added to the lease or rental price of a U-drive-it vehicle or motorcycle the vehicle
14 and thereby be paid by the person to whom it is leased or rented.
15 A tax levied under this Article applies regardless of whether the a retailer who leases or rents
16 the U-drive-it vehicle or motorcycle has the option of paying the gross receipts tax under
17 G.S. 105-187.5 has elected to pay the optional gross receipts tax on the lease or rental receipts
18 from the vehicle. A tax levied under this Article must be paid to the Authority that levied the tax
19 by the date an optional the gross receipts tax levied under G.S. 105-187.5 is payable or would be
20 payable to the Secretary of Revenue under G.S. 105-187.5 if the retailer who leases or rents the
21 U-drive-it vehicle or motorcycle had elected to pay the optional gross receipts tax.
22 (c) Penalties and Remedies. – The penalties and remedies that apply to local sales and
23 use taxes levied under Subchapter VIII of this Chapter apply to a tax levied under this Article.
24 The board of trustees of an Authority may exercise any power the Secretary of Revenue or a
25 board of county commissioners may exercise in collecting local sales and use taxes."
26 SECTION 7.3.(a) G.S. 20-280.15 reads as rewritten:
27 "§ 20-280.15. Definitions.
28 The following definitions apply in this Article:
29 (1) Airport operator. – As defined in G.S. 20-280.1.
30 (2) Peer-to-peer vehicle sharing. – The authorized use of a shared vehicle by an
31 individual other than the shared vehicle owner through a peer-to-peer vehicle
32 sharing program.
33 (3) Peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program. – A business platform that connects
34 shared registered vehicle owners that have not made an election under
35 G.S. 105-187.5 with drivers to enable the sharing of vehicles for financial
36 consideration.
37 (4) Shared vehicle. – A vehicle that is available for sharing through a peer-to-peer
38 vehicle sharing program.
39 (5) Shared vehicle owner. – The registered owner of a shared vehicle that is made
40 available for sharing through a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.
41 (6) Vehicle Peer-to-peer vehicle sharing provider. – The A person or entity that
42 operates, facilitates, or administers the provision of personal vehicle sharing
43 through a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program."
44 SECTION 7.3.(b) G.S. 20-280.17 reads as rewritten:
45 "§ 20-280.17. Airport operators.
46 An airport operator may (i) charge peer-to-peer vehicle sharing programs providers a
47 reasonable fee for the use of the airport's facility, (ii) require an identifying decal be displayed
48 on all shared vehicles that operate on airport property, (iii) require the purchase and use of
49 equipment or establish other appropriate mechanisms for monitoring and auditing compliance,
50 including having a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program provider provide data for purposes of
DRH10248-SVxf-3B Page 21

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 monitoring and auditing compliance, and (iv) designate a location where shared vehicles may
2 stage on the airport operator's facility."
3 SECTION 7.4. This Part becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to gross
4 receipts derived from rentals or leases billed on or after that date.
5
6 PART VIII. EFFECTIVE DATE
7 SECTION 8. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
8 law.
